cat << 'HELP'
 Commands
  mkcd <dir>          create directory and cd into it
  take <url|dir>      git clone + cd, or mkdir + cd
  tmp [name]          throwaway workspace (tmp help for more)
  port <number>       show what's listening on a TCP port
  regen               rebuild zsh plugin cache
  reload              restart shell

 Aliases
  ls                  eza with icons
  ll / la             long listing
  cat                 bat (syntax highlighted)
  vim / vi            nvim
  lg                  lazygit
  ld                  lazydocker
  zi                  zoxide interactive cd
  d                   show directory stack
  1-9                 jump to directory stack entry

 Keybindings
  Ctrl+L              clear screen
  Ctrl+Z              toggle suspend/resume (replaces fg)
  Ctrl+F              fix last mistyped command
  ↑/↓                 history search (prefix match)
  Alt+b / Alt+f       move word backward/forward
  Alt+d               te word forward
  Ctrl+W              delete word backward

 Bookmarks
  ~code               ~/code
  ~dots               ~/dotfiles
  ~dl                 ~/Downloads
  ~tmp                temp workspaces (cleared on reboot)
